[assistant] Fixed the failing test.
[assistant] 
[assistant] Cause:
[assistant] - `sendObject(...)` went beyond the target dynamic-access path and attempted to write a WebSocket frame.
[assistant] - That requires Tomcat’s `Transformation` chain to be initialized, but this lightweight `WsSession` setup does not initialize it, causing the `NullPointerException`.
[assistant] 
[assistant] Change:
[assistant] - Updated `WsRemoteEndpointImplBaseTest` to stop after constructing `WsSession`.
[assistant] - Session construction still reaches `WsRemoteEndpointImplBase.setEncoders(...)`, which covers the remaining dynamic-access call sites:
[assistant]   - `Class#getConstructor(...)`
[assistant]   - `Constructor#newInstance(...)`
[assistant] - The test now asserts that the configured encoder was constructed and initialized.
[assistant] 
[assistant] Commit amended:
[assistant] - `70a5a87a28 Add websocket remote endpoint encoder coverage`
[assistant] 
[assistant] I did not rerun tests, per the original instruction. The pre-existing untracked metadata directory remains untouched:
[assistant] - `metadata/org.apache.tomcat.embed/tomcat-embed-websocket/9.0.83/`
[assistant-event] text_end
